The Trump Administration’s attack on Title X promises to block health care access for some four million people—mostly poor, mostly women.
Title X funding provides the most vulnerable people in the United States with health care.
Title X funding provides the most vulnerable people in the United States with health care.
A third of U.S. women with low incomes depend on Title X clinics for their contraception.
And that could mean the responsibility for ensuring adequate health care access for vulnerable populations—like other protections of reproductive rights—will eventually fall to the states.